answers.body_markdown:
The problem is in the impossibility of finding the dependency of &quot;org/glassfish/jersey/server/monitoring/ApplicationEventListener&quot; at deployment.

A possible solution is to include in the war the dependency

 

    &lt;dependency&gt; 
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.glassfish.jersey.core&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;jersey-server&lt;/artifactId&gt; 
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

To disable the JerseyServerMetricsAutoConfiguration class in a Spring Boot application, you can use the @SpringBootApplication annotation with the exclude attribute. Here&#39;s an example:

    @SpringBootApplication(exclude = JerseyServerMetricsAutoConfiguration.class)
    public class MyApplication {
        // ...
    }
In the example above, the JerseyServerMetricsAutoConfiguration class is excluded from the application configuration by specifying it in the exclude attribute of the @SpringBootApplication annotation.

Alternatively, you can use the @EnableAutoConfiguration annotation with the exclude attribute to achieve the same result:

    @Configuration
    @EnableAutoConfiguration(exclude = JerseyServerMetricsAutoConfiguration.class)
    public class MyApplication {
        // ...
    }

